nd post-Soviet Russia, seeking to explain why an often romanticized medieval past remains potent in Russian politics, society, and culture today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aImperial Russia.  aMiddle Ages.  aRussian politics.  aSoviet Russia.  aUkraine.  apost-Soviet Russia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311133235240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781802702408?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781802702408423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781802702408/original  a978-3-11-133235-2  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles